%S A379695 1,1,1,2,6,40,560,17024,1066496,135307264,34496249856,17626824704000,
%T A379695 18032060589408256,36911538015915999232,151152657111915754946560,
%U A379695 1238091228945093466831978496,20283647846218731237811773505536,664634282779152972863264105275850752
%N A379695 Number of equivalence classes of regular vines in dimension n.
%C A379695 a(n) is also the number of non-isomorphic MAT-labelings of complete graph K_n. (Tran, Tran, Tsujie, 2024, Theorem 3.1).
%C A379695 From _Shuhei Tsujie_, May 22 2026: (Start)
%C A379695 a(n) is also the number of non-isomorphic maximal Arrow's single-peaked domains.
%C A379695 a(n) is also the number of non-isomorphic (n,3)-extremal lattices. (End)
%D A379695 H. Joe, R. M. Cooke, and D. Kurowicka, Regular Vines: Generation Algorithm and Number of Equivalence Classes, in D. Kurowicka and H. Joe, eds., Dependence Modeling, World Scientific, 2010, pp. 219-231 (§10.3).
%D A379695 H. M. Tran, T. N. Tran, and S. Tsujie, Vines and MAT-labeled graphs, Forum of Mathematics, Sigma, Vol. 12 (2024), Art. e128.
%H A379695 Shuhei Tsujie, <a href="/A379695/b379695.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..83</a>
%H A379695 Bogdan Chornomaz, <a href="https://hal.science/hal-01175633">Counting extremal lattices</a>, HAL Preprint hal-01175633, 2015.
%H A379695 Klas Markström, Søren Riis, and Bei Zhou, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2401.12547">Arrow's single peaked domains, richness, and domains for plurality and the Borda count</a>, arXiv:2401.12547 [econ.TH], 2024.
%H A379695 Hung Manh Tran, Tan Nhat Tran, and Shuhei Tsujie, <a href="https://www.mat.univie.ac.at/~slc/wpapers/FPSAC2024/12.html">Vines and MAT-labeled graphs</a>, Séminaire Lotharingien de Combinatoire 91B (2024) Article #12, 12 pp.
%H A379695 Hung Manh Tran, Tan Nhat Tran, and Shuhei Tsujie, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2605.20629">An axiomatic framework from splitting and merging in MAT-labeled graphs, vines, and single-peaked domains</a>, arXiv:2605.20629 [math.CO], 2026.
%F A379695 a(1) = a(2) = a(3) = 1; for n >= 4, a(n) = 2^((n-2)*(n-3)/2 - 1) * Sum_{k=0..m} c(k) * 2^(-k*(n-k-2)), where m = floor(n/2) - 1, and c(k) = 2 if k = m else 1. - _Shuhei Tsujie_, May 22 2026
%K A379695 nonn,changed
